body:
Hi there,

Trying to use iVerilog to simulate real-number models using `wire real` ports - sometimes these are arranged in busses.

However, when we do so there are two problems.

Problem 1 is that these real bus ports are not auto-dumped to VCD with the `$dumpvars(0,top);` command. They can be dumped to VCD only by explicitly naming each one - e.g. `$dumpvars(0,top.foo[3],top.foo[2],top.foo[1],top.foo[0]);`.

Problem 2 is that real bus variables are inaccessible through cocotb. For example if I use the code below in cocotb I cannot write to the real variable A using something like `dut.A[1].value=2.0`.

These don't seem like massive problems - can someone help guide me to where to look in the iVerilog source code to try and understand these problems?

Thanks,

Simon
```

`timescale 1ns/1ns

module adder( A, C);
`ifndef _2AA
    input wire real A [1:0];
    input wire real B;
    output wire real C;
    
    assign C = A[1] + A[0];
`endif
endmodule 

module top ( );
    real A [1:0];
    real C;
    wire real wr_A [1:0];
    adder dut(
        .A(wr_A),
        .C(C)
    );
    assign wr_A=A;
    
    initial begin
        A[0]=1;
        A[1]=4;        

        #100;
        A[0]=3;
        #100;        
        A[1]=2;
    end

    initial begin
        $dumpfile("adder.vcd");
        $dumpvars(0,top);
        #400;
        $finish();
    end
endmodule
```

